  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nBuilding on `FreeBSD 12.1-RELEASE`, I hit some limit during the build of crates `eth1` and `lighthouse`. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\n   Compiling lighthouse v1.0.1 (/usr/home/gballet/src/lighthouse/lighthouse)\r\nerror: reached the type-length limit while instantiating `std::pin::Pin::<&mut std::future...::Future>::poll::{{closure}}#0]>`\r\n    |\r\n    = note: consider adding a `#![type_length_limit=\"1405659\"]` attribute to your crate\r\n\r\nerror: aborting due to previous error\r\n\r\nerror: failed to compile `lighthouse v1.0.1 (/usr/home/gballet/src/lighthouse/lighthouse)`, intermediate artifacts can be found at `/usr/home/gballet/src/lighthouse/target`\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\n`stable` @ `5a3b94cbb4a82f999c2deb5c45146eaf58146957`\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nAs a workaround, I have set:\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![type_length_limit = \"20364955\"]\r\n```\r\nat the beginning of both `beacon_node/eth1/src/lib.rs` and `lighthouse/src/main.rs`.",
